Creating a **smooth Snake game in C** that uses **images for animation** is a great project that involves several components: **graphics rendering**, **input handling**, **game logic**, and **animation**. Since C doesn't have built-in graphics support, you'll need to use a **graphics library** like **SDL2** (Simple DirectMedia Layer) or **SFML** (Simple and Fast Multimedia Library). For this example, I'll use **SDL2**, which is widely used and well-documented.

---

## ✅ Step-by-Step Guide to Create a Smooth Snake Game with Images in C (Using SDL2)

### 📦 1. Install SDL2
First, you need to install SDL2 on your system. Here are instructions for different OS:

#### Linux:
```bash
sudo apt-get install libsdl2-dev
```

#### macOS (using Homebrew):
```bash
brew install sdl2
```

#### Windows:
Download the SDL2 development libraries from [https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php](https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php) and set up the environment accordingly.

---

### 🧰 2. Project Structure

Create a folder for your project and add the following files:

```
snake-game/
├── main.c
├── snake.h
├── images/
│   ├── snake_head.png
│   ├── snake_body.png
│   ├── apple.png
│   └── background.png
└── CMakeLists.txt (optional)
```

